{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"b46df018-2c87-4043-a17a-bf0e4cca7518","content":"Here's what I found:\n\n**`my_app/views.py:3`** — `datetime.now()`\n\n```python\nnow = datetime.now()\n```\n\nThis is an **untestable static call** — you can't control the return value in tests without monkeypatching.\n\n### Recommended fix\n\nUse Django's `django.utils.timezone.now` instead, which is the idiomatic Django approach and easily mockable:\n\n```python\nfrom django.utils import timezone\n\ndef index(request):\n    now = timezone.now()\n    return render(request, 'index.html', {'time': now})\n```\n\nThis also gives you **timezone-aware** datetimes (important if `USE_TZ = True`). In tests you can freeze time with `freezegun` or `unittest.mock.patch(\"django.utils.timezone.now\")`.\n\nThat's the only instance in the project. Want me to apply the fix?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"bbb1b0fc-eef4-4e06-9bd2-6b21116f0182","outputTokens":218,"requestId":"6800:7B46E:1AC3189:1E46DD8:69FD5079"},"id":"e04628da-82ad-4d6a-8552-0539ba2d30ed","timestamp":"2026-05-08T02:54:56.166Z","parentId":"c43bab4c-3302-4b22-8b47-f08f2a589742"}
